						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the temple of Kallēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vīra-Ballāḷa II—A.D. 1187-88.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">16th regnal year of Vīra-Ballāḷadēva, Plavaṅga,</hi> which corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1187-88.</hi> Further details of the date are lost. It records the death of <hi rend="bold">Dāsōja,</hi> son of the goldsmith <hi rend="bold">[Sō]vōja,</hi> in a cattle-raid and registers a gift of land by some <hi rend="italic">Gauḍas</hi> for the hero-stone set up by his brothers <hi rend="bold">Masaḷōja</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Kētōja.</hi> The record is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
